==English==

{{rft|Invalid punctuation in title, but where should article go?  <br>Also, the heading "Tag" should be "Interjection", right?}}

===Tag===
'''[[don't]]/[[doesn't]]''' ''one'''''?'''<BR>
'''[[do]]/[[does]]''' ''one'' '''[[not]]?'''

# ''[[request|Request]] for [[confirmation]] that converts an affirmative present tense sentence into a [[question]]. Expects [[agreement]] in a "yes" answer.''
#:<tt>“</tt>Timmy loves ice cream, '''does he not'''?<tt>”</tt>
#:<tt>“</tt>You have the airline tickets, '''don't you'''?<tt>”</tt>

====Usage notes====
As a tag, always used with an object pronoun substituting for the subject. Number distinguishes between ''do'' and ''does'', ''don't'' and ''doesn't''.

===Tag===
'''doesn't [[one]]?'''<BR>
'''does one not?'''

# (''rare'') ''Request for confirmation (as above).''
#:<tt>“</tt>One suspects only a foreigner would say this, '''doesn't one'''?<tt>”</tt>

